        "id": 2296625,
        "name": "Ryan Caughey",
        "username": "RyanC",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/ryanc/{size}/731_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-11-13T16:39:09.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is a new producer for me and probably the best Givry I\u2019ve had. I don\u2019t know if it\u2019s that 2015 is brilliant, or that Lumpp is brilliant, but this is the best Burgundy QPR I can recall, and it\u2019s hard to imagine there\u2019s a better $37 Pinot made anywhere on Earth. I immediately ran out and bought more.</p>\n<p><span class=\"bbcode-u\"><strong>2015 Fran\u00e7ois Lumpp Givry 1er Cru Clos du Cras Long</strong></span><br>\nMy first '15 Burg and it\u2019s a beauty with just about everything you could want in a young Burg. Expressive Pinot nose introduces a a hyper-fresh, bright, crunchy, and juicy palate of impressively concentrated brambly fruit. A tinge of cranberry hints at a tip-top Cru Beajuolais. Medium-bodied and finessed with a velvet texture. This is all about the fruit now but there\u2019s every reason to expect a long and graceful life, with greater heights ahead. <strong>93</strong></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T01:40:49.978Z",
